  "texts": [
    "Notably, the representation within each format can also vary significantly.",
    "For instance, when it comes to modeling requirements, representations might take the form of UML, systems modeling language (SysML), goal-oriented models, etc.",
    "Although guideline standards like ISO/IEC/IEEE 29148:2018 [67] and easy approach to requirements syntax (EARS) [68] are provided, their adoption in the industry is limited.",
    "It is reported that nearly half (47%) of RE practitioners are unaware of these standards [69].",
    "Consequently, the representation of requirements often aligns with individual writing practices rather than standardized guidelines."
